Audit the diff below for application-security vulnerabilities aligned with the
OWASP Top 10. Look for:
  - Injection: SQL, command (os.system / subprocess shell), template, LDAP,
    path traversal, XXE, SSRF
  - Authentication / authorization gaps: missing access checks, weak JWT
    validation, broad CORS, privilege escalation
  - Secrets management: hardcoded credentials, keys, or tokens
  - Cryptographic weaknesses: MD5 / SHA1 / DES, hardcoded keys, weak randomness
  - Security misconfiguration and unsafe deserialization

Only report vulnerabilities you can tie to a concrete line in the diff.

For each issue, produce a ReviewFinding with:
  severity:   CRITICAL | IMPORTANT | SUGGESTION
  file, line: location (line >= 1)
  category:   security
  title:      10-120 chars
  body:       1-3 sentences naming the vulnerability class and the attack vector
  suggested_fix: optional code or guidance
  confidence: 0.0-1.0
